questions.question_text: When does a RADIUS server send an Access-Challenge packet?

choices.B: The server requires more information from the user, such as the token code for two-factor authentication.
choices.D: The user account is not found in the server.
choices.A: The server does not have the user credentials yet.

discussion.content:
Selected Answer: B
The answer is B
I don't see option A. But B and D are incorrect.Correct should be A and C

comments.content: A. Primary unit stops sending HA heartbeat keepalives.

discussion.content: C is correct , but I dont see A

questions.question_text:
Which the following events can trigger the election of a new primary unit in a HA cluster? (Choose two.)
.
B. The FortiGuard license for the primary unit is updated.
C. One of the monitored interfaces in the primary unit is disconnected.
D. A secondary unit is removed from the HA cluster.

The logs in a FSSO collector agent (CA) are showing the following error: failed to connect to registry: PIKA1026 (192.168.12.232)
What can be the reason for this error?

discussion.content:
Selected Answer: C
It's C as per: https://community.fortinet.com/t5/FortiGate/FSAE-Common-Log-messages-and-recommendations/ta-p/193054?externalID=FD30548

choices.A: The CA cannot resolve the name of the workstation.
choices.B: The FortiGate cannot resolve the name of the workstation.
choices.C: The remote registry service is not running in the workstation 192.168.12.232.
choices.D: The CA cannot reach the FortiGate with the IP address 192.168.12.232.

discussion.content: A, B and C are correct

A, B and C is correct

Enterprise firewall 6.4 Study Guide Pg120
A, B and C are correct

questions.question_text: Which of the following statements are true regarding the SIP session helper and the SIP application layer gateway (ALG)? (Choose three.)

choices.B: SIP ALG supports SIP HA failover; SIP helper does not.
choices.A: SIP session helper runs in the kernel; SIP ALG runs as a user space process.
choices.C: SIP ALG supports SIP over IPv6; SIP helper does not.
choices.E: SIP helper supports SIP over TCP and UDP; SIP ALG supports only SIP over UDP.
choices.D: SIP ALG can create expected sessions for media traffic; SIP helper does not.

discussion.content:
Selected Answer: D
D is correct
